diff_act: 8.alert the operator when attempting to execute functions beyond the permitted interaction level

regen.absent_element: system response to unsuccessful self-test or configuration checks
regen.new_specification: The TCS shall alert the operator and enter a safe mode if the system self-test or configuration checks are unsuccessful.

regen.absent_element: system response after assessing achievable interaction levels and prohibiting higher levels
regen.new_specification: The TCS shall alert the operator and log the event when a prohibited interaction level is attempted during startup

regen.absent_element: system response when interaction level assessment fails
regen.new_specification: The TCS shall notify the operator and enter a safe mode if the interaction level assessment fails to determine achievable levels.

label: The TCS shall inform the operator if the operator attempts to execute a function prohibited as a result of the determined level of interaction.
absence: Warning for execution of functions prohibited according to determined interaction levels
